<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920786>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 1–11. Mitinha neri, sp. nov., paratype specimens. 1. Habitus, lateral view, female. 2. Antenna, male; 3. Wing, male; 4. Epandrium and cerci, male, posterior view; 5. Male terminalia, dorsal; 6. Phallus, lateral view; 7, Hypandrium and gonostylus, dorsal view; 8, Hypandrium and gonostylus, lateral view; 9. Vaginal furca and sperm pump, female; 10. Apex of spermathecal duct; 11. Mid part of apical spermathecal duct with microvilli tubules. Abbreviations: AAAS, anterior arm of aedeagal sheath; BPH, basiphallus; CE, cercus; DPH, distiphallus; EJ AP, ejaculatory apodeme; EP, epandrium; GST, gonostylus; HY, hypandrium; LEP, lateral ejaculatory process; DPH, distiphallus; SP, sperm pump; T8, tergosternite VIII; VF, vaginal furca." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4920786/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920790>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 21–25. Mythicomyiidae. 21. Antennae of Pieza, from Piauí, Brazil; 22. Wing of Mythenteles, from Evenhuis (2002a); 23. Wing of Reissa, from Greathead & Evenhuis (2001); 24. Wing of Pieza, from Piauí, Brazil; 25. Wing of Mythicomyia, from Piauí, Brazil." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4920790/files/figure.png" .

